<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="259" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,979,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">
Material studied: 
<typeStatus box="[396,494,1015,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">holotype</typeStatus>
male and 
<typeStatus box="[609,705,1016,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">paratype</typeStatus>
female, with the data specified in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1988 a) [Cecidomyiidae of the subfamily Lestremiinae (Diptera) from the Crimea.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1988 (1), 74 - 76." type="journal article" year="1988" yearSuffix="a">
Berest 
<number box="[151,211,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1988.0">1988</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,979,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">
The genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[423,521,1087,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName box="[619,774,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emarginata">
<emphasis box="[619,774,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. emarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distorted (
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" box="[934,1188,1087,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1988 a) [Cecidomyiidae of the subfamily Lestremiinae (Diptera) from the Crimea.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1988 (1), 74 - 76." type="journal article" year="1988" yearSuffix="a">
Berest 
<number box="[1014,1073,1088,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1988.0">1988</number>
a: fig. 
<number box="[1142,1188,1087,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but still well enough preserved to show the structures characteristic of 
<emphasis box="[716,848,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. f u ng i co l a</emphasis>
: the thick gonostylus with a tooth-like apical spine and a deep subapical concavity, and the elongate tegmen with a pair of U-shaped subapical cavities (
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1938 c) On the British Lestremiinae, with notes on exotic species. 7. (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 7, 253 - 265." type="journal article" year="1938" yearSuffix="c">
Edwards 
<number box="[151,211,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1938.0">1938</number>
c
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[287,316,1196,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="28.0">28</number>
b, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof" box="[348,517,1196,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Jaschhof, M. (1998) Revision der &quot; Lestremiinae &quot; (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) der Holarktis. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 4, 1 - 552." type="journal article" year="1998">
Jaschhof 
<number box="[457,517,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[581,626,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="218.0">218</number>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof" box="[641,810,1196,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Jaschhof, M. (2001) On the Lestremiinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Japan. Part 2: Tribe Peromyiini Kleesattel, 1979. Esakia, 41, 37 - 147." type="journal article" year="2001">
Jaschhof 
<number box="[750,810,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[874,906,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="47.0">47</number>
). Berest’s (
<number box="[1039,1097,1196,1220]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1988.0">1988</number>
a) differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emarginata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. emarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes reference to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yukawa, 1967" authorityName="Yukawa" authorityYear="1967" box="[513,831,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispina">
<emphasis box="[513,660,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. brevispina</emphasis>
Yukawa, 
<number box="[775,831,1231,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1967.0">1967</number>
</taxonomicName>
rather than to 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1139,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungicola">
<emphasis box="[1003,1139,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. fungicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa" box="[1262,1436,1231,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="262" refString="Yukawa, J. (1971) A revision of the Japanese gall midges (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae). Memoirs of the Faculty of Agriculture, Kagoshima University, 8, 1 - 203." type="journal article" year="1971">
Yukawa (
<number box="[1370,1428,1232,1256]" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[355,499,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispina">
<emphasis box="[355,499,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. brevispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[563,696,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Peromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungicola">
<emphasis box="[563,696,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="259">P. fungicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
